{1 utf16-positions}
- Spec: {!page-"feature-utf16-positions"}
- Implementation: {!Lsp_lib.Util.byte_offset_of_position} and
  {!Lsp_lib.Util.position_of_byte_offset} take [?encoding] (default
  [Utf16]); server advertises [positionEncoding = utf-16].
- Test: {!Lsp_lib.Util}'s "utf-16 position encoding" module, plus a
  UTF-16 cursor case in {!module-Lsp_lib.Go_to_definition.test}.
- Not yet done: offering utf-8/utf-32 negotiation, and UTF-16 for the
  go-to-definition target column ([position_of_textloc], needs the
  target file's content).

