{1 attribute-anchors}
- Spec: {!page-"feature-attribute-anchors"}
- Core: {!Oystermark.Vault.Index.extract_attr_ids} (collection),
  {!Oystermark.Vault.Resolve.resolve} ([Attr]/[Curr_attr] cases).
- Consumers: {!module-Lsp_lib.Go_to_definition} and
  {!module-Lsp_lib.Find_references} (attribute anchor targets).
- Test: {!module-Lsp_lib.Go_to_definition.test},
  {!module-Lsp_lib.Find_references.test}, and
  [Oystermark.Vault.Index]'s [extract_attr_ids] expect test.
- Column precision: go-to-definition returns a [(line, character)]
  position; inline anchors land mid-line. The [character] is a UTF-16
  column decoded from the target file's body (read via [read_file] for
  cross-file, the buffer for self-file) by
  {!Lsp_lib.Util.position_of_textloc}. Spec
  {!page-"feature-go-to-definition".target_position}.
- Diagnostics: duplicate anchor ids are reported (see the
  {{!page-"feature-diagnostics".duplicate_ids}diagnostics spec}).
- Section extraction: {!Oystermark.Parse.Extract.get_block_by_attr_id}
  feeds both embed ([![[note#id]]]) and hover, so an attribute anchor
  previews/embeds its containing block instead of the whole file.
- Frontmatter positions: {!Oystermark.Parse.Frontmatter.blank_frontmatter}
  blanks (rather than strips) the frontmatter region before parsing, so
  every parsed [Textloc] is full-file-relative. This fixes line/byte
  positions for frontmatter files across all LSP features (gtd,
  find-references, diagnostics, hover ranges) at once.
- Follow-ups (not yet done): attribute ids in completion (completion is
  itself unimplemented).
